theorem interior_nonempty_of_closed_nonempty_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hClosed : IsClosed A) (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) (hA : A.Nonempty) :
    (interior A).Nonempty := by
  classical
  by_contra hIntEmpty
  -- Translate the negated non‐emptiness into an equality to `∅`.
  have hIntEq : interior (A : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) :=
    (Set.not_nonempty_iff_eq_empty).1 hIntEmpty
  -- `P1` for a closed set yields `closure (interior A) = A`.
  have hEq : closure (interior (A : Set X)) = (A : Set X) :=
    (Topology.P1_closed_iff_closure_interior_eq (A := A) hClosed).1 hP1
  -- Hence, using `hIntEq`, we deduce `A = ∅`.
  have hAEmpty : (A : Set X) = ∅ := by
    simpa [hIntEq, closure_empty] using hEq
  -- This contradicts the assumed non‐emptiness of `A`.
  have hContr : False := by
    simpa [hAEmpty] using hA
  exact hContr
